                            <comment id="13677" author="jay" created="Wed, 4 May 2011 11:55:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The AutoTest passed at: &lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/c8fd045c-75f4-11e0-a1b3-52540025f9af&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/c8fd045c-75f4-11e0-a1b3-52540025f9af&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is a failure on ost-pools:test-18. I think this is a known issue, and I have filed a ticket at &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-276&quot; title=&quot;ost-pools: test-18 Degradation with missing pool is 26.07 % (&amp;gt; 15 %)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-276&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-276&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please check it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13348" author="jay" created="Tue, 26 Apr 2011 22:12:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve verified the patch at: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,462&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,462&lt;/a&gt;. It can fix the problem. W/o this patch, obdfilter-survey.sh hits this problem often, after applying this patch, this problem has never been hit again.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
